# Backend (Laravel 11) Conventions

## PHP & tooling
- PHP 8.3, strict types (`declare(strict_types=1);` at the top of every file).
- PHPStan level 8. No baselines, no `@phpstan-ignore`.
- Pest for tests, not PHPUnit syntax.
- Pint for formatting (`vendor/bin/pint`).

## Folder structure
```
apps/backend/
├── app/
│   ├── Domain/                  Pure domain logic, no I/O
│   │   ├── Fifo/                CutoffCalculator, LiveState, Decision
│   │   ├── Queue/               Queue position arithmetic
│   │   └── Announcement/        Template rendering
│   ├── Http/
│   │   ├── Controllers/Api/V1/  Thin controllers, one action per method
│   │   ├── Requests/            Form request validation
│   │   ├── Resources/           API response shaping + ApiResponse trait
│   │   └── Middleware/
│   ├── Jobs/                    Queue jobs (idempotent, retry-aware)
│   ├── Models/                  Eloquent models
│   ├── Mqtt/                    MQTT subscriber + handlers
│   ├── Broadcasting/            Reverb events
│   ├── Services/                Cross-cutting services (AuditLogger, etc.)
│   ├── Policies/                Authorization policies
│   └── Console/Commands/        Artisan commands
├── database/
│   ├── migrations/              Timestamped, append-only
│   ├── seeders/                 Idempotent seeders
│   └── factories/               Model factories for tests
├── routes/
│   ├── api.php                  Versioned: /api/v1/...
│   └── channels.php             Reverb channel auth
├── scripts/lua/                 Redis Lua scripts
└── tests/
    ├── Feature/                 Full-stack tests
    └── Unit/                    Domain tests
```

## Controller pattern

Controllers MUST be thin. Domain logic lives in `App\Domain\*` or `App\Services\*`.

```php
<?php declare(strict_types=1);

namespace App\Http\Controllers\Api\V1;

use App\Http\Controllers\Controller;
use App\Http\Requests\UpdateQuotaRequest;
use App\Http\Resources\LocationStateResource;
use App\Services\QuotaService;
use Illuminate\Http\JsonResponse;

final class QuotaController extends Controller
{
    public function __construct(private readonly QuotaService $quotas) {}

    public function update(UpdateQuotaRequest $request, int $locationId): JsonResponse
    {
        $state = $this->quotas->updateQuota(
            tenantId: $request->user()->tenant_id,
            locationId: $locationId,
            quotaDate: $request->validated('quota_date'),
            quota: $request->validated('quota'),
            actor: $request->user(),
        );

        return LocationStateResource::make($state)->response();
    }
}
```

## Model pattern

Strict `$fillable`, `$casts`, and `BelongsToTenant` where applicable.

```php
<?php declare(strict_types=1);

namespace App\Models;

use App\Models\Concerns\BelongsToTenant;
use Illuminate\Database\Eloquent\Model;
use Illuminate\Database\Eloquent\Relations\BelongsTo;
use Illuminate\Database\Eloquent\Relations\HasMany;

final class Location extends Model
{
    use BelongsToTenant;

    protected $primaryKey = 'location_id';

    protected $fillable = [
        'tenant_id', 'name', 'short_code', 'address',
        'latitude', 'longitude', 'opens_at', 'closes_at',
        'default_quota', 'mode', 'festival_mode', 'status',
    ];

    protected $casts = [
        'latitude'      => 'decimal:7',
        'longitude'     => 'decimal:7',
        'default_quota' => 'integer',
        'festival_mode' => 'boolean',
    ];

    public function tenant(): BelongsTo
    {
        return $this->belongsTo(Tenant::class, 'tenant_id', 'tenant_id');
    }

    public function quotas(): HasMany
    {
        return $this->hasMany(DailyQuota::class, 'location_id', 'location_id');
    }
}
```

## Migrations

```php
<?php declare(strict_types=1);

use Illuminate\Database\Migrations\Migration;
use Illuminate\Database\Schema\Blueprint;
use Illuminate\Support\Facades\Schema;

return new class extends Migration {
    public function up(): void
    {
        Schema::create('locations', function (Blueprint $table) {
            $table->bigIncrements('location_id');
            $table->unsignedBigInteger('tenant_id');
            $table->string('name', 120);
            $table->string('short_code', 20);
            // ... rest of columns
            $table->timestamps();

            $table->unique(['tenant_id', 'short_code'], 'uq_locations_tenant_code');
            $table->index('tenant_id', 'idx_locations_tenant');

            $table->foreign('tenant_id', 'fk_locations_tenant')
                ->references('tenant_id')->on('tenants')
                ->restrictOnDelete();
        });
    }

    public function down(): void
    {
        Schema::dropIfExists('locations');
    }
};
```

## Test pattern (Pest)

```php
<?php declare(strict_types=1);

use App\Domain\Fifo\CutoffCalculator;
use App\Domain\Fifo\LiveState;

it('declares cutoff when queue length exceeds remaining tokens', function () {
    $state = new LiveState(
        quota: 5000, issued: 3840,
        queueHead: 3841, queueTail: 5210,
        issuanceRatePerMin: 18.4, arrivalRatePerMin: 22.1,
    );

    $decision = (new CutoffCalculator())->decide($state);

    expect($decision->status)->toBe('cutoff_declared');
    expect($decision->cutoff)->toBe(5000);
});
```

## What NOT to do

- ❌ Don't put FIFO logic in a controller or job
- ❌ Don't call external HTTP from a request handler — always queue
- ❌ Don't bypass `ApiResponse` envelope
- ❌ Don't use `dd()`, `var_dump()`, `print_r()` in committed code
- ❌ Don't add a job without making it idempotent
- ❌ Don't modify a deployed migration
- ❌ Don't query an operational table without `tenant_id` scope
